<paragraph id="8BB5DE45CA6D5A62F0ECFDDFFBD16B04" blockId="12.[151,1437,534,986]" box="[151,1085,534,560]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="B97E0257CA6D5A62F0ECFDDFFEE16B04" bold="true" box="[151,269,534,560]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Material:</emphasis>
<collectionCode id="ED1B4680CA6D5A62F16EFDDFFE816B04" LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34992" box="[277,365,534,560]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34992" name="National Museum of Natural History, Naturalis" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">RMNH</collectionCode>
Coel. 
<number id="3DC2CC62CA6D5A62F1C1FDDFFDEA6B04" box="[442,518,534,560]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="38769.0">38769</number>
, one colony, Farur Island, coll. S.A. Mohtarami.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3108DCECA6D5A62F0BDFDF4FAFF6A87" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB5DE45CA6D5A62F0BDFDF4FE116B90" blockId="12.[151,1437,534,986]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="B97E0257CA6D5A62F0BDFDF4FEB36B63" bold="true" box="[198,351,573,599]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Description.</emphasis>
The colony is 
<quantity id="4CF273A0CA6D5A62F272FDF4FDBD6B63" box="[521,593,573,599]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="cm" value="22.0">22 cm</quantity>
wide and 
<quantity id="4CF273A0CA6D5A62F2B3FDF4FCE36B63" box="[712,783,573,599]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="cm" value="11.0">11 cm</quantity>
high, and a holdfast is present (
<figureCitation id="1331C2C0CA6D5A62F404FDF4FB2A6B63" box="[1151,1222,573,599]" captionStart="FIGURE 7. a" captionStartId="13.[151,255,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[175,1418,197,1952]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[175,1419,197,1953]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 7. a, RMNH Coel. 38768, holotype of Astrogorgia fruticosa n. sp.; b, RMNH Coel. 38769, Echinogorgia sp. a; c, RMNH Coel. 38770, Echinogorgia sp. b; d, RMNH Coel. 38771, Echinogorgia sp. b. Scales 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186750/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC2CC62CA6D5A62F4CDFDF4FB2A6B63" box="[1206,1222,573,599]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
b). Branching is in one plane, anastomoses are frequent, forming a network. Polyps are situated all around the branches, the calyces are low, dome-shaped.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB5DE45CA6D5A62F0BEFD78FBD66BC6" blockId="12.[151,1437,534,986]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Polyps are retracted, with a collaret and points formed from flattened spindles, up to 
<quantity id="4CF273A0CA6D5A62F4C8FD78FAF06BFF" box="[1203,1308,689,715]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.20 mm</quantity>
long, with sparse tuberculation (
<figureCitation id="1331C2C0CA6D5A62F1E9FD11FE356BC6" box="[402,473,728,754]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[172,1415,194,1950]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[172,1416,194,1950]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. RMNH Coel. 38769, Echinogorgia sp. a: a polyp spindles; b, spindles of interior; c, thornscales of surface layer; d, capstan derivatives of the subsurface layer." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186752/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC2CC62CA6D5A62F1B2FD11FE356BC6" box="[457,473,728,754]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
a). The point spindles have one end slightly dentate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB5DE45CA6D5A62F0BEFD37FD8E6AB8" blockId="12.[151,1437,534,986]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Surface layer of the coenenchyme has thornscales, up to 
<quantity id="4CF273A0CA6D5A62F30CFD37FC0E6A2C" box="[887,994,766,792]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.40 mm</quantity>
long; additionally a few unilaterally spinose spindles are present (
<figureCitation id="1331C2C0CA6D5A62F188FCECFDAB6A0B" box="[499,583,805,831]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[172,1415,194,1950]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[172,1416,194,1950]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. RMNH Coel. 38769, Echinogorgia sp. a: a polyp spindles; b, spindles of interior; c, thornscales of surface layer; d, capstan derivatives of the subsurface layer." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186752/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Figs. 
<number id="3DC2CC62CA6D5A62F24CFCECFDAB6A0B" box="[567,583,805,831]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
c, 
<number id="3DC2CC62CA6D5A62F219FCECFD6C6A0B" box="[610,640,805,831]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="10.0">10</number>
a–b). The inner layer has spindles, up to 
<quantity id="4CF273A0CA6D5A62F41CFCECFB3D6A0B" box="[1127,1233,805,831]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.40 mm</quantity>
long, many with one or two side branches (
<figureCitation id="1331C2C0CA6D5A62F1ACFC85FDCA6A52" box="[471,550,844,870]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[172,1415,194,1950]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[172,1416,194,1950]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. RMNH Coel. 38769, Echinogorgia sp. a: a polyp spindles; b, spindles of interior; c, thornscales of surface layer; d, capstan derivatives of the subsurface layer." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186752/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Figs 
<number id="3DC2CC62CA6D5A62F26DFC85FDCA6A52" box="[534,550,844,870]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
b, 
<number id="3DC2CC62CA6D5A62F23FFC85FD896A52" box="[580,613,844,870]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="10.0">10</number>
c). Furthermore, small derivatives of capstans are present; length of these sclerites up to 
<quantity id="4CF273A0CA6D5A62F1FFFCBBFE006AB8" box="[388,492,882,908]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.10 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation id="1331C2C0CA6D5A62F186FCBBFDAF6AB8" box="[509,579,882,908]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[172,1415,194,1950]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[172,1416,194,1950]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. RMNH Coel. 38769, Echinogorgia sp. a: a polyp spindles; b, spindles of interior; c, thornscales of surface layer; d, capstan derivatives of the subsurface layer." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186752/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC2CC62CA6D5A62F248FCBBFDAF6AB8" box="[563,579,882,908]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
d).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB5DE45CA6D5A62F0BEFC51FAFF6A87" blockId="12.[151,1437,534,986]" box="[197,1299,920,947]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="B97E0257CA6D5A62F0BEFC51FECD6A86" bold="true" box="[197,289,920,946]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Colour.</emphasis>
Alive, the colony was purple in colour, preserved it is brown. Sclerites are colourless.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3108DCECA6D5A62F0BEFC76FAD76AEE" box="[197,1339,959,986]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB5DE45CA6D5A62F0BEFC76FAD76AEE" blockId="12.[151,1437,534,986]" box="[197,1339,959,986]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
